  "notes": "Amharic Ethiopic (Ge'ez) script. Abugida where each character encodes consonant + vowel; 7 vowel orders per consonant row. Ejectives: Tʼ, Čʼ, Pʼ, Tsʼ are phonemic. The 6th order (ə-vowel) is the inherent vowel. Ä, ʕ (Ayin) present in traditional script but may be realized as /ʔ/ or silent in colloquial speech.",
